name: Ritz Classic Panjim

reviews.review_text:
Warm ambience here. And the fish thali is to die for.
The food comes very fast and nice hospitality.
The beer batter fry squids very lovely..
Do try the like soda if possible
The serradura wasn't thick but rather a little too watery

Ritz Classic Panjim is a legendary Fish Thali place which should be in to-do list of every person visiting Goa. I have been coming here for last 10 years and never disappointed by their Chonak Fish Thali. Mr. Bhaskar Shetty (Manager) is as hospitable as always serving with big smile. However, this time around we had a very bad experience with one of their waiter who is bald. He was extremely rude to all of our queries regarding fish availability and freshness before placing the order, gave weird looks to us and spoilt the entire experince for us due to his rude attitude. Will never come to this place again to see this person for how badly he treated us during our entire meal time and rather visit Ritz's other outlet.

We ordered here very good food. The taste was very nice. However, the downside of it is the crowd here you must stand at least for 30 minutes to get your turn. We were literally pissed off standing so much, however, just because this has that go authentic food so we waited long.
We ordered crab garlic, which was very good and tasted also, nice.
I like too much the fish curry, which was so good to have with the rice. The caramel pudding was not that great, but yeah, fine to eat one time. The soul kadi is must try.

description:
### Dining at Ritz Classic Panjim: A Goan Culinary Journey

Nestled in the bustling Corlim Industrial Estate, Ritz Classic Panjim shines as a beloved culinary gem, boasting an impressive **4.2 rating** from **16,759 reviews**. Known primarily for its authentic Goan flavors, the restaurant has become synonymous with their signature **fish thali**, a centerpiece of their menu that has captured the heart of both locals and tourists alike. With tags highlighting its specialties — including *thali* (frequently mentioned 1,224 times), *Goan* cuisine (865), *crab masala* (87), and *solkadi* (70) — it’s clear that Ritz Classic is dedicated to showcasing the tastes of Goa.

### Ambiance & Design

Upon entrance, guests are greeted by a **warm ambiance** that feels both inviting and relaxed. The décor features touches of Goan culture, with vibrant colors and decor that blend seamlessly with rustic charm. Customer photos capture the cozy setting, enhanced by soft lighting that adds to the leisurely dining experience. While there are no specific mentions of music in the reviews, the atmosphere appears inviting for gatherings with friends or family, fostering a community feel that encourages patrons to linger over their meals.

### Menu & Culinary Experience

Ritz Classic is renowned for its sumptuous seafood offerings, with the **Chonak Fish Thali** consistently receiving high praise. Guests rave about the **beer-battered fried squid** and **crab garlic**, which are described as delightful and bursting with flavor. One review especially notes the **fish curry** paired perfectly with rice, while the **solkadi** is highlighted as a *must-try*— an authentic Goan drink known for its refreshing qualities. However, a few guests have noted that while some dishes like the **serradura** (a traditional Goan dessert) could use improvement, overall, the culinary experience remains strong. The presentation of the dishes, as captured in customer photos, showcases a vibrant palette that is as appealing to the eyes as it is to the palate.

### Customer Experience & Service

The hospitality at Ritz Classic receives mixed reviews. While many diners have praised the friendliness and efficiency of the staff — with specific commendations for Mr. Bhaskar Shetty, the manager, whose welcoming demeanor sets a positive tone — there are notable exceptions. A recent experience highlighted poor service from one waiter, whose rudeness tarnished an otherwise enjoyable visit. Such contrasting experiences underline the importance of consistent service alongside culinary excellence. As for dining logistics, it’s worth noting that peak times may lead to longer waiting periods, sometimes pushing guests to stand in line for over 30 minutes. Yet, many agree that the authentic flavors justify the wait.

### Popularity & Reviews

Ritz Classic Panjim enjoys a loyal following, cemented by years of consistent quality and exceptional flavors. Its reputation as a **legendary fish thali destination** is echoed across various reviews, reinforcing its status as a must-visit for anyone in Goa. Despite the occasional dip in service, the overwhelming majority of feedback reflects a strong affection for the restaurant, indicating that it remains a go-to venue for Goan cuisine enthusiasts.

### Utilizing Visual Content

The images shared by customers depict not only the beautifully presented dishes but also contribute to the vibrant atmosphere of the restaurant. For instance, the eye-catching snaps of the thali, with its array of colorful curries and accompaniments, truly reflect the culinary artistry that patrons rave about. Other photos capture the inviting ambiance and decor, affirming Ritz Classic’s commitment to creating an authentic dining environment.

In summary, Ritz Classic Panjim emerges as a culinary staple in Goa, celebrated for its traditional fish thali and other Goan dishes. While the dining experience may vary with service dynamics, the rich flavors and warm atmosphere leave an indelible mark on every visitor, making it a worthy addition to one’s culinary adventures in Goa.
